title: Improve java documentation by explaining "magic" constants like ""save/control_dependency""
body_html:
In your examples here there is a statement:

sess.runner()
     .feed("save/Const", checkpointPrefix)
     .addTarget("save/control_dependency")
     .run();

Can you explain somewhere in documentation what is the "magic" constants used there and list all the variants of them somewhere?

body:
In your examples [here](https://github.com/tensorflow/models/blob/master/samples/languages/java/training/src/main/java/Train.java) there is a statement:
```
sess.runner()
     .feed("save/Const", checkpointPrefix)
     .addTarget("save/control_dependency")
     .run();
```
Can you explain somewhere in documentation what is the "magic" constants used there and list all the variants of them somewhere?
